# References

> External authoritative sources that this project depends on. SpecSwarm consults these
> at key moments to avoid fabricating content that already exists or guessing at
> behavior that has a canonical reference. All sections are OPTIONAL — leave one
> empty if it doesn't apply.
>
> Generated by `/ss:init`. Hand-edit anytime; SpecSwarm re-reads on every relevant
> command invocation.

---

## Spec corpus

> Markdown documents that contain authoritative project specifications. SpecSwarm
> reads these (via the `Read` tool, just like a human would) during `/ss:specify`
> and `/ss:clarify` to extract relevant sections instead of generating from scratch.
>
> List paths relative to the project root, or absolute paths. Glob patterns OK.

<!-- Examples (delete or replace):
- path: docs/PRD.md
- path: docs/architecture/*.md
- path: ../shared-spec/INTERACTION-FLOWS.md
-->

