## Reference codebases

> Read-only codebases that serve as behavioral specifications — legacy systems
> being ported, prototype codebases being formalized, competitor binaries reverse-
> engineered, or sibling projects with shared conventions. SpecSwarm verifies each
> reference resolves at session start and warns if missing.
>
> Each entry needs:
> - `name`: short identifier used in audit logs
> - `path`: filesystem path to the codebase root (absolute OR relative to project root)
> - `verify-file`: a file that should exist inside the reference; used as a presence check
> - `rationale`: one-line note on why this reference matters (shows up in warnings)

<!-- Examples (delete or replace):
- name: legacy-app
  path: ../../legacy-app
  verify-file: src/main.py
  rationale: Behavioral spec for the API port; preserve endpoint semantics
-->

